Not elevated by these dignities, which even Made him ador’d and honour'd. All his thought Was to please Him, from Whom all this was given, To Whom he owed his breath. He chiefly sought To be beloved of all, and largely gave, That he the poor’s good wishes so might have.

He knew his riches were on him bestow'd To relieve others’ wants, he knew the end Of his preferment·, that his wealth was owed By him which made and doth the world defend.
